721869f-a.text: Nassau Street, at the N.E. corner of Cedar Street. The building known as the Old New York Post Office was formerly Dutch Reformed Church. The site is now occupied by the New York Mutual Life Insurance Company. About 1880. Brown Brothers.
721869f-a.folder: Nassau Street & Cedar Street, Manhattan, NY

721870f-a.text:
Nassau Street, at the South West corner of Cedar Street, also shown is Cedar Street, South Side, west from Nassau Street, to but not including Broadway.  The Building shown is occupied by the Bank of North America.  August Belmont is also located at this site.  About 1890.

No record of Photographer.
